//Architecture
/*
 * by default in our HW->OS- we have jvm installed without jvm we cant run java code
 * JAVA is platform independent -it means it will run an any machine so if you have jvm in our OS it will Run
 * JVM IS platform-dependent for every machine there are different jvm's
 * 
 * 
 * source code (.java) -> compiler (.javac)-> byte code > (.class) -> Machine code
 * 
 * JDK = JVM+JRE
 * JVM = classloader +bytecode verfiers +intrepreter + JIT
 * JRE = JVM+ other runtime  Libraries+packages
 * 
 * 
 * 
 * 
 * 
 * */
